{"questionId":"3005731","questionHtml":"<p>There exist values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> for which the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mi>x</mi></math> and the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> do have intersection points. The following table gives three intervals for the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>.<br><br></p>\n<table style=\"height:92px;border-color:#000000;width:344.65px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;text-align:center;height:17px;\">Interval</td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;text-align:center;height:17px;\">Number of intersection points</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:15px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;text-align:center;height:15px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;text-align:center;height:15px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;text-align:center;height:17px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;text-align:center;height:17px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;text-align:center;height:17px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;text-align:center;height:17px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>By investigating the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mi>x</mi></math> for different values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>, write down the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<table style=\"height:92px;border-color:#ffffff;width:344.65px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;height:17px;text-align:center;\">Interval</td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;height:17px;text-align:center;\">Number of intersection points</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:15px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;height:15px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;height:15px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;height:17px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;height:17px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px;\">\n<td style=\"width:82px;height:17px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:242.65px;height:17px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&